-- Lau’s Girlfriends Seek HK$11.2 Billion of AIA IPO, Standard Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-27T20:01:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/joseph-lau-s-girlfriends-seek-hk-11-2-billion-of-aia-stock-standard-says.html
Yvonne Lui Lai-Kwan and Chan Ho-wan,
girlfriends of  Chinese Estates Holdings Ltd . Chairman  Joseph Lau , have applied for HK$11.2 billion -- HK$5.6 billion each --
of shares in AIA Group Ltd.’s Hong Kong initial public offering,
the Standard reported.  The applications account for more than 50 percent of the
portion of the share sale set aside for individual investors,
the Hong Kong-based English-language newspaper said today,
citing unidentified people. The women will receive at least
HK$509.6 million of shares each, the Standard said.  Lau has denied that the applications were made on his
behalf, the newspaper said, citing an unidentified spokesman for
Lau.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  